default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAlthough cycling is relatively (but
default not exceptionally) risky for the user compared with most
default 
defaultother transport modes, the opposite is true if you consider how little risk cyclists impose on
default 
defaultother people.  In 2012, 98
default% of killed or seriously injured (KSI) pedestrians in urban areas
default 
default(i.e. where
default pedestrians are most likely to be) resulted from collisions with motor vehicles.
