default revealed that, per urban
default mile travelled (excluding motorways, where cyclists and pedestrians are prohibited), cars are 2.3 times more likely than cycles to be involved in a pedestrian injury, and 3.2 times as likely 
defaultto be involved in a pedestrian fatality.  The ratios of danger p
